    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
        Demo application.
        • creates some demo MobilePhoneContract data using init()
        • prints the test data using print(List)
        • sorts them by natural order
        • prints them again (sorted) using print(List)
        • filters MobilePhoneContracts, keeping those with customer's home address "Wien" using filter(List, Matcher)
        • prints the filtered MobilePhoneContracts again using print(List)
        • prints the filtered and sorted MobilePhoneContracts using print(List)
        • exports the filtered and sorted MobilePhoneContracts to file "MobilePlans_Wien_by_additionalFee.txt" and displays the number of deliveries exported using export(List, String)
        • tops up all prepaid cards with 20€ and prints the test data using print(List)
        Parameters:
        args - (not used)

      • export

        public static int export​(java.util.List<MobilePhoneContract> mobilePhoneContracts,
                         java.lang.String filename)
        Saves several MobilePhoneContracts to file. The MobilePhoneContracts are saved in their standard format (standard string representation) one per line. This functions does not throw any IOException, instead handles them internally, printing an error message if exporting fails.
        Parameters:
        mobilePhoneContracts - the MobilePhoneContracts to export
        filename - the name of the target file
        Returns:
        number of MobilePhoneContracts successfully exported

      • filter

        public static <T> java.util.List<T> filter​(java.util.List<T> list,
                                           Matcher<? super T> m)
        filters a collection of entities with a certain filter. a newly created list of entities containing only those that match. The entities themselves are not duplicated.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the entities
        Parameters:
        list - the original entities to filter
        m - the filter
        Returns:
        the entities that match

      • print

        public static void print​(java.util.List<MobilePhoneContract> mobilePhoneContracts)
        Prints MobilePhoneContracts line by line.

        Adds a short header before printing the String representation of all MobilePhoneContracts line by line. For a single MobilePhoneContract the standard string representation provided by MobilePhoneContract.toString() is used.

        Parameters:
        mobilePhoneContracts - the MobilePhoneContracts to print.
        Hint:
        provided
